6000|$|... 6. It {{is easy to}} say a prayer, but {{difficult}} truly to pray. It is not length, not eloquence, <b>that</b> makes <b>prayer.</b> Though {{there be}} no more than 'My Father!' if the heart rise with it, <b>that</b> is <b>prayer.</b> 'Prayer is an offering up of our DESIRES unto God.'--Ed.|$|R
